\id AMO Matupi Chin Standard Bible
\h AMOS
\toc1 AMOS
\toc2 Amos
\toc3 Amo
\mt1 AMOS
\mt2 (The Book of Amos)
\is1 Amos Cabu Kawng
\im Amos loh boiva saelhung a dawn doela Boeipa kah ol he 760 \sc b.c.\sc* vaengah a thui. Amos he Judah ram tuithim ah a cun dae Pathen loh tlangpuei kah Israel ram la ol thui ham a tueih. Syria, Philistia, Phoenicia, Edom, Ammon, Moab, neh Judah he a cawh vetih dan a tat ni. Tedae Israel hlanglen rhoek loh khodaeng neh mangdaeng te a yoop dongah amih soah kah dantatnah kawng te a sen la a thui. Israel sokah laitloeknah kawng te othang panga a tueng sak. Kaisih loh buh boeih a yoop ni, diklai pum te hmai loh boeih a hlawp ni. Mikrhael rhui a toe te khaw Israel ca rhoek he Pathen kah uepomnah tangtlaeng dongah hing pawh a ti. Voeihang dongah kah thaihhmin loh Israel ca rhoek a poci ham yoei coeng a ti. Bethel im neh bawkkung rhoek khaw cungku pawn ni a ti. Israel ca rhoek te namtom taengah taekyak la om ni. A hnukkhueng ah ngaiuepnah om, ram te koep a thoh vetih pilnam khaw hoeih ni.
\iot Sawt Yoeinah
\io1 Namtom soah olcaeknah \ior 1. 1—3. 2\ior*
\io1 Israel neh Samaria a phae ni \ior 3. 3—6. 14\ior*
\io1 Israel sokah dantatnah panga \ior 7. 1—9. 10\ior*
\io1 Israel ham hmailong khosae \ior 9. 11-15\ior*
